---
import BaseLayout from '../components/layout/BaseLayout.astro';
import '../styles/prose.css';
---

<BaseLayout title="About — James Ming" description="About James Ming — research, writing, and interests.">
  <div class="page-wrapper">
    <div class="about-shell">
      <article class="prose about-prose">
        <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
        <h1>James Ming</h1>

        <p class="lede about-lede">
          I work at the intersection of machine learning, economics, and complex systems —
          trying to understand how things actually work, not just how they're described.
        </p>

        <p>
          This site is where I do my thinking in public. Posts tend to be long, careful, and
          equation-heavy. I write about ideas I've had to work hard to understand, in the hope
          that writing them down makes them clearer — for me first, and for you second.
        </p>

        <p>
          Most posts are either deep technical explainers (score-based generative models, mechanism
          design, renormalization group methods) or cross-domain essays that trace a single idea
          across fields — the kind of structural similarity that emerges when you look at information
          theory, statistical mechanics, and evolutionary biology side by side.
        </p>

        <hr />

        <h2>Research interests</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Generative models — diffusion, flow matching, score-based methods</li>
          <li>Inference and uncertainty — Bayesian nonparametrics, calibration, epistemic humility</li>
          <li>Economics as a formal science — mechanism design, market microstructure, information economics</li>
          <li>Computational biology — statistical methods in genomics, evolutionary dynamics</li>
          <li>Physics of learning — statistical mechanics of neural networks, renormalization, phase transitions</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>What you'll find here</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Research notes:</strong> working through papers in detail, often with
            derivations filled in and claims stress-tested
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Technical essays:</strong> first-principles treatments of ideas I think are
            under-explained in the literature
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Cross-domain connections:</strong> structural analogies between seemingly
            unrelated fields — thermodynamics and information, evolution and gradient descent
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Occasional working drafts:</strong> rougher notes on things I'm actively
            thinking through
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Elsewhere</h2>
        <p>
          Non-technical writing — career, strategy, broader reflections — lives on
          <a href="https://approximatelycorrect.substack.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
            Approximately Correct
          </a>.
          Code lives on
          <a href="https://github.com/jamesmingliangang" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>.
        </p>

        <p class="contact-note">
          For research questions or corrections: reach me via
          <a href="https://github.com/jamesmingliangang" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>.
          I read everything; I reply slowly.
        </p>
      </article>

      <aside class="about-rail">
        <div class="rail-block">
          <p class="rail-label">Domains</p>
          <ul class="rail-list">
            <li>Machine learning</li>
            <li>Economics</li>
            <li>Physics</li>
            <li>Biology</li>
            <li>Chemistry</li>
            <li>Business strategy</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="rail-block">
          <p class="rail-label">This site</p>
          <ul class="rail-list">
            <li>Built with <a href="https://astro.build" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Astro</a></li>
            <li>Math via KaTeX</li>
            <li>Hosted on GitHub Pages</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="rail-block">
          <p class="rail-label">Links</p>
          <ul class="rail-list">
            <li><a href="https://approximatelycorrect.substack.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Substack</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://github.com/jamesmingliangang" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a></li>
            <li><a href="/rss.xml">RSS</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-wrapper {
    padding-top: var(--space-16);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-20);
  }

  .about-shell {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, var(--prose-width)) minmax(14rem, var(--rail-width));
    column-gap: var(--space-12);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .about-prose h1 {
    margin-top: var(--space-2);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .about-lede {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
  }

  .contact-note {
    font-size: 0.9em;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  /* Rail */
  .about-rail {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-8);
    padding-top: 5.5rem; /* align with prose after eyebrow + h1 */
    position: sticky;
    top: calc(var(--header-height) + var(--space-8));
  }

  .rail-block {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding-top: var(--space-4);
  }

  .rail-label {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .rail-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-2);
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .rail-list a {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .rail-list a:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  @media (max-width: 980px) {
    .about-shell {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .about-rail {
      position: static;
      padding-top: 0;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      padding-top: var(--space-8);
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(160px, 1fr));
      gap: var(--space-6);
    }

    .rail-block {
      border-top: none;
      padding-top: 0;
    }
  }
</style>
